sub_title: Enhancing communication and collaboration in diverse workplaces
summary:
I am sure you know successful executive teams who, while acknowledging the value of cultural diversity, face multiple hurdles: less compelling leadership; ineffective communication styles; misaligned priorities. 

Mastering cultural uncertainty is winning the game. My name is Catherine Macquart-Martin. I help executive teams to navigate across cultures, multiply their impact in a vast array of intercultural contexts, and yield a competitive advantage.

I do that by consulting, training, and coaching. I think this is important because mutual understanding, trust and delivering collaboration are needed to face the challenges of our interconnected and volatile world.

When these hurdles keep you up at night, call me or connect with me via my LinkedIn or visit my website.
